r a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BURN-VICTIM-1st-Write     01-04 0327
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BURN-VICTIM-1st-Writethru-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FIRE CLAIMS SECOND YOUNG VICTIM
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Editors: Retransmitting to restore dropped word, ``fire,'' in
lead.) 
BY DEBORAH SULLIVAN  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES -- Patrick Crawford, a 7-year-old boy who was
severely injured in a Christmas tree fire Thursday in Val Verde,
Calif., died Sunday at the Grossman Burn Center at Sherman Oaks
Hospital in suburban Sherman Oaks, Calif. His 17-year-old
half-brother, Shawn Williams, had died Saturday after surgery at
the same facility.
</P>
<P>
   The boys were burned in a fire that broke out shortly after 8
a.m. Dec. 31 in the Santa Clarita Valley north of the Los Angeles
metropolitan area.
</P>
<P>
   Grossman Burn Center spokesman Larry Weinberg said Patrick went
into respiratory failure at 5:23 a.m. Sunday and was pronounced
dead at 6:25 a.m.
</P>
<P>
   ``He was in extremely critical condition with third-degree burns
over 65 percent of body and significant smoke-inhalation damage to
his lungs,'' Weinberg said.
</P>
<P>
   Given the boy's small size and severe injuries, his chances of
survival had been slight, Weinberg said. While young children heal
faster than adults, he said, the loss of fluid is more devastating
to a child's body. Burns and smoke damage to Patrick's lungs
eventually overwhelmed him.
</P>
<P>
   ``One of the pediatricians -- part of the team that treated him
-- said that, given the extent of his burns and extent of
smoke-inhalation damage, the mortality rate for a child in his
condition would probably be about 90 percent,'' Weinberg said.
</P>
<P>
   The older half-brother's friend, Patricia Lynn Martin, 20, and
the boys' aunt, Dawn Carter, 45, were also injured in the fire.
</P>
<P>
   The Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department has declared that
the fire's origins are suspicious, and arson investigators were
assigned to the case. Sgt. David Halm said Sunday that the
investigation is continuing.
</P>
<P>
   X X X &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
