<HEADLINE>
BLEDSOE PINED TO PLAY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By DAN SHAUGHNESSY  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   JACKSONVILLE, Fla. _ He was one of the first players to exit the
locker room after Sunday's playoff loss to the Jaguars. And why
not? Drew Bledsoe didn't have to shower after the game. He never
got in uniform.
</P>
<P>
   With a protective pin still sticking out of his right index
finger, the quarterback watched from the sideline Sunday as the
Patriots went down, 25-10. It was the third straight game he
missed, but it hurt more because he was unable to play in a playoff
game for the first time in his career.
</P>
<P>
   While Scott Zolak struggled against the Jaguars, making No. 11
look more valuable than ever, Bledsoe wore headphones and sent
signals from the sideline. In a white T-shirt and khaki pants, the
Patriots' franchise player looked downright coach-like. There were
times when he seemed to be in charge of the entire team.
</P>
<P>
   It's been a rough few weeks for Bledsoe. As he walked toward the
team bus, he was asked if he was glad to see the season finally end
or just looking forward to starting again next year.
</P>
<P>
   ``Looking forward to next year, definitely,'' said Bledsoe. ``I
can't wait for the next one to start.''
</P>
<P>
   He signed a few autographs as he walked. This is not easy when
you have little use of the index finger on your writing hand.
</P>
<P>
   And what about the fate of coach Pete Carroll.
</P>
<P>
   ``His record speaks for itself,'' said the quarterback. ``He's
made the playoffs two years in a row. And he didn't allow all the
distractions to get to us. There were a lot of things that could
have made us quit, but we didn't, and that's because of him.''
</P>
<P>
   Bledsoe is a favorite of owner Robert Kraft. It's much like the
Carl Yastrzemski/Tom Yawkey relationship, in which Yaz was
considered coach-maker/breaker. Does Bledsoe want Carroll to
return?
</P>
<P>
   ``Yeah, definitely,'' he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
