<HEADER>
A6119 &Cx1f; var-z
u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-R-HEALTHCARE-REVIEW-2     01-04 1075
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-R-HEALTHCARE-REVIEW-2TAKES-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FOR MANAGED CARE, FREE-MARKET SHOCK 
</HEADLINE>
 
 (Repeating for all needing. (The Week in Review) 
(bl) 
 By REED ABELSON    
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   When Prudential Insurance Company of America decided in December
to sell its health-care operations to Aetna Inc., it was the latest
example of a company that could not make money caring for sick
people. Despite Prudential's best efforts, the business, mostly in
