<P>
   GEEWAX-Y2K-COLUMN _ No matter what happens in Washington or
around the world, most Americans are in the mood to be happy. Maybe
it has something to do with the thrill of preparing for a new
century. Today's optimism in many ways mirrors the surge in
confidence the nation experienced in 1899. The technology wizard
and the new citizen may again be fueling our optimism. (Geewax,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
