   Y2K-DISASTER (Albany, N.Y.) _ In a cluttered attic corner in his
Poestenkill, N.Y., home, 36-year-old Doug Roseberger is quietly
preparing for disaster. He's learned all he could about Year 2000,
or Y2K, threats: power outages, food shortages, a major recession
or, depending on whose web site you read, the entire collapse of
civilization. Whatever happens, Roseberger wants to be ready. By
ALAN WECHSLER.
