</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WITLESS `AVENGERS'; TOO-BRIGHT LYMON BIOPIC 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``The Avengers'' _ Ralph Fiennes and Uma Thurman
are no threat to the original ``Avengers,'' Patrick Macnee and
Diana Rigg. This is a great case of movies thinking that high-tech
production values, instead of sharp dialogue, are what made the TV
show a success. Even Sean Connery, as the mad villain, can't save
this stupid film. Get ``The Avengers'' TV episodes that have been
out for several months.
</P>
<P>
   ``Why Do Fools Fall in Love'' _ Frankie Lyman loved singing and
women, not necessarily in that order. Three ex-wives, led by a fine
performance by Halle Berry, excavate their memories of the man and
his music with mixed results. Actually, there's too much bright
lights, big city for a character who had some very dark moments.
</P>
<P>
   ``Baseketball'' _ Trey Parker and Matt Stone, the creators of
the phenomenally successful ``South Park'' on Comedy Central, try
to hit one out of the park with this farce. But it's a big swing
and a strikeout. Unlike other gross-out comedies, this one's
distasteful without being funny.
</P>
<P>
   ``Montana'' _ Whoever cast this movie must have been crazy. Kyra
Sedgwick, one of our most delicate actresses, plays a gangland
assassin with laughable results. A great supporting cast _ Robbie
Coltrane, Stanley Tucci, and Robin Tunney _ is wasted because the
central premise is so far off.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Jan. 5: ``Out of Sight,'' ``The Rescuers,''
``How Stella Got Her Groove Back,'' ``Every Mother's Fear,'' ``Dr.
Who: The Mind of Evil,'' ``Disturbing Behavior,'' ``Project
Grizzly,'' ``Scarred City.'' Jan. 12: ``Wilde,'' ``Love and Death
on Long Island,'' ``The Truman Show,'' ``Our Mutual Friend,'' ``p''
``Dance With Me,'' ``Henry Fool,'' ``Fireworks,'' ``Sing and Dance
With Barney,'' ``The Wubbulous World of Dr. Seuss.'' Jan. 19:
``Smoke Signals,'' ``Invasion Earth,'' ``Mafia!,'' ``Because of
Him,'' ``The Amazing Mrs. Holliday,'' ``Slums of Beverly Hills,''
``Evidence of Blood,'' ``Buffalo Island,'' ``Little City,''
``Buffalo 66.'' Jan. 26: ``Kurt and Courtney,'' ``Whatever,''
``Cube,'' ``Rush Hour.'' Feb. 2: ``There's Something About Mary,''
