<P>
   GA-LEGIS-HEALTH _ Health care reform remains a huge issue, both
in terms of state expenses and for individuals. The rural hospitals
remain want assurances they're going to be able to afford to stay
around; the medical lobby will want something from Roy in terms of
managed care revisions -- perhaps a separate medical regulatory
board. What can we look for in this session? (AMiller, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 42 inches.
</P>
<P>
   GA-CITIES-Y2K _ Just how prepared/unprepared are Georgia towns
and hamlets for the coming milennium changeover? Mike Hale,
Georgia's chief of information technology, says municipal electric
and water systems across the state are not computer-ready for Dec.
31, 1999. We call a sampling of towns at the compass corners of
Georgia, and in between, to see what they have or haven't done
about the situation. (Smith, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
