   MIDSIZED-CITIES (Cincinnati) _ Much of the American economy's
strength is showing up in mid-sized cities like Cincinnati,
Memphis, Austin and Kansas City. Public spending plays a role, and
so do tax breaks and other subsidies that are aggressively offered
to coax companies to locate or expand in these cities, diversifying
the local economies in the process. But the main engine is a
plentiful pool of less-expensive workers. With Photo. By Louis
Uchitelle.
