   The goal of expanding the regional club, the Association of
South East Asian Nations (ASEAN) to include all ten countries of
the geographical area may well be achieved in December 1998, with
Cambodia's admission. But the coup there in July 1997, and
Myanmar's international isolation, have raised questions about
