<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients)  
. 
The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``e'' entertainment news file. For questions, contact Jimmy
Johnson at the Daily News, (818) 713-3695. 
. 
CRUSADE-TV (Bloom) _ Somewhere Einstein, Oppenheimer and Feynman
are surely in high-RPM rotation in their graves over what passes
these days for the science in many science-fiction shows on
television. They can stop twirling in their tombs. One of Big
Science's great bastions, the Jet Propulsion Laboratory in
Pasadena, is helping put the facts back into science fiction TV in
the new series ``Crusade.'' By David Bloom. 
. 

