</P>
<P>
   The biggest worry is that the new European Central Bank, eager
to build up its anti-inflationary credibility, will try to be
tougher than the Bundesbank and be slow to cut interest rates if
necessary.
</P>
<P>
   To judge how severe the global slowdown will be in 1999, keep
your eye on four crucial factors: First, will Japan's $500 billion
