<HEADLINE>
BY DESIGN: FOR WINTER VACATIONS
</HEADLINE>
  (ms) 
 By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Anyone who is lucky enough to be heading for a warm place in the
sun can find lightweight pants in the newest shape: wide-legged and
cropped anywhere from below the knee to above the ankle.
</P>
<P>
   Neiman Marcus has cropped pants in eggplant or beige linen
($270) and with a drawstring waist in pinstripes ($280) by
Eskandar; in beige stretch viscose ($150) by Margaret M; in black
or stone stretch cotton ($85) by Work Order; in a polyester blend
with a drawstring waist ($148), in charcoal pinstripes ($148) and
in a lightweight wool blend ($158), all by Laundry, and in a slate
linen blend ($155) or a stone cotton blend ($175) by Theory.
</P>
<P>
   At Barneys New York there are white cotton cropped sailor pants
($425) by Marc Jacobs; white cotton slit-pocket pants by John
Bartlett ($350); cotton glen plaid by Narciso Rodriguez ($505);
fine-wale blue corduroy by Jill Stuart ($195), and gray cotton by
Theory ($145). &QL;
</P>
