of Tuesday, Jan. 5, and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact Tom Hicks at the Daily News, (818)
713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   INFOMERCIALS (Los Angeles) _ If there's a lesson to be learned
from the four top grossing infomercials of 1998, it's that peeling
off pounds is the No. 1 obsession for coach potatoes across
America. By Gregory J. Wilcox.
</P>
<P>
   MINIMED-STOCK (Los Angeles) _ After a run-up that saw the
company's share price climb more than $50 in two months, medical
devices manufacturer MiniMed Inc. stock dropped Monday after the
company was downgraded by two analysts. By Ben Sullivan.
</P>
<P>
   LLOYD-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Ken LLoyd, Ph.D., a specialist in
organizational behavior, answers readers' questions on getting
ahead in or just staying afloat in today's business world.
</P>
