<P>
   CUBA-U.S. (Washington) _ The United States is prepared to let
Cuban citizens receive more money from American friends and family,
sell them more American food and medicine, permit more direct
flights and renew direct mail service from the United States, and
let the Baltimore Orioles and the Cuban national baseball team play
ball in March, senior administration officials say. By Tim Weiner.
(We plan to move the story by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
