million or more to settle discrimination claims. (Scheduled to move
by 9 p.m. ET in ``w'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-LABOR (New York) _ NBA owners reject the union's latest
collective bargaining proposal, and the league's Labor Committee
takes the first step toward scrapping the entire 1998-1999 season.
By Mike Wise. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``s'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   BOTTOM
</P>
<P>
   SAFRICA-WEDDINGS (Kwambonambi, South Africa) _ Across South
Africa, in black townships and in rural villages, tribal marriage
ceremonies are under assault, feeling the pull of young women who
want not only white dresses but also what they believe is the
better deal that Western weddings hold out for them. In many cases,
the weddings have become an expensive, and sometimes trying, mix of
both cultures. By Suzanne Daley. (The story has moved in ``i'' news
file.) Story runs under 3-column photo.
</P>
