NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR TUESDAY, JANUARY 5
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Tuesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-IMPEACH-ASSESS-NYT (moved on Sunday, January 3)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, January 3,
about arguments for an impeachment trial misattributed a quotation
concerning the Senate's ``constitutional responsibility'' to hold a
trial. The statement was made by Representative Asa Hutchinson,
Republican of Arkansas, not by his brother, Senator Tim Hutchinson,
also an Arkansas Republican.
</P>
<P>
   BC-INSURANCE-YEAR2000-NYT (moved on Sunday, Dec. 13, 1998)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Dec. 13,
1998, about a lawsuit over insurance liability for disruptions
caused by the Year 2000 computer problem referred incorrectly to
the relationship between Keane Inc. and the defendant, Source Data
Inc. Keane purchased some of Source Data's assets in 1995, but does
not own Source Data and is not involved in the suit.
</P>
