<SLUG> BC-FBC-FIESTANOTES-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    BCS might modify big-bowl criteria
 &HT;    By Tony Barnhart
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEMPE, Ariz. _ Fans had a number complaints about the new Bowl
Championship Series (BCS) this season, but one most-often heard was
that the system gave automatic slots in the big bowls to teams like
Syracuse (8-3) simply because they were conference champions.
</P>
<P>
   SEC commissioner Roy Kramer said Monday that the BCS might
discuss modifying that stance in the future.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've always felt it was important to take care of the
conference champions because those titles should mean something,''
Kramer said in an address before the Football Writers Association
of America. Kramer also said the BCS might someday consider moving
all four of its games back to New Year's Day.
</P>
<P>
   Rare misses
</P>
<P>
   Tennessee's Jeff Hall missed a 33-yard field goal on Tennessee's
first possession after the Vols had driven to the Florida State 16.
It was the first time all season that Hall had missed from 35 yards
or less after making nine in a row.... An extra-point try by
Florida State's Sebastian Janikowski was blocked in the second
quarter. It was only the second miss all season for the sophomore
who was the Lou Groza Award winner.
</P>
<P>
   Boos for the VP
</P>
<P>
   Vice President Al Gore, who wants to be the next president of
the United States, may have lost some votes from native
Tennesseans. Gore timed his arrival at Sun Devil Stadium just
perfectly to keep about 100 Volunteers fans from getting to their
seats as they tried to board the stadium elevator. Secret Service
agents blocked off a long corridor leading to the elevators 15
minutes before he arrived and 15 minutes after Gore was safely in
his luxury seat.
</P>
<P>
   Said one angry fan: ``I paid $135 apiece for these tickets. If I
miss the kickoff I'm not going to vote for the guy. I don't care
where he's from!''
</P>
<P>
   Another backup QB
</P>
<P>
   FSU played with backup quarterback Marcus Outzen, who took over
when Chris Weinke suffered a neck injury on Nov. 7. Coming to the
desert with a backup quarterback is nothing new for coach Bobby
Bowden. In 1983 and 1984 FSU played at Arizona State, and in both
games the Seminoles' No. 1 quarterback was knocked out of the game.
Florida State won both games.
</P>
<P>
   Worth noting
</P>
<P>
   Tennessee defensive tackle Ron Green was carried off the field
in the first quarter with a sprained knee.... Florida State had two
roughing the kicker penalties in the first half. The second took a
Tennessee field goal off the board and the Vols scored for a 7-0
lead.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
