<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CLAIBORNE WILL MAKE IT OFFICIAL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC linebacker Chris Claiborne is expected to
announce today that he is forgoing his senior year and will make
himself available for the NFL draft.
</P>
<P>
   Claiborne had lunch with USC coach Paul Hackett on Monday but
did not tell Hackett his intentions even though he has already made
his decision.
</P>
<P>
   ``We just talked. We had a little meeting,'' Claiborne said.
</P>
<P>
   Claiborne said the subject of whether he decided to turn pro
never came up in the conversation.
</P>
<P>
   ``No. He didn't ask me,'' Claiborne said. ``He represented his
side. Maybe he wanted to wait (until today).''
</P>
<P>
   Claiborne will hold a press conference today at USC to make his
official announcement.
</P>
<P>
   Although Claiborne has tried to keep his decision secret, he let
his guard down last week in El Paso and said that he intended to
hire an agent soon. A close friend, asked Monday if Claiborne had
made up his mind to turn pro, said his decision was so obvious,
``don't try to break your neck figuring this one out.''
</P>
<P>
   Claiborne said Monday that he is ``leaning heavily to one side
of the coin.''
</P>
<P>
   An interesting choice of words, since he will make millions if
he is one of the top five draft picks, as he has been projected by
some analysts.
</P>
<P>
   Another sign Claiborne is leaving: He said Monday that he did
not believe he could raise his NFL stock by returning for another
season.
</P>
<P>
   Claiborne attended Monday's USC-Arizona basketball game with
former teammate Brian Kelly, who plays for the Tampa Bay
Buccaneers.
</P>
<P>
   What about Soward? USC is hopeful that wide receiver R. Jay
Soward will also attend today's press conference and announce that
he is staying.
</P>
<P>
   Soward told his father after the Sun Bowl last week he was
returning for his senior year, but USC would prefer an official
statement before Friday's NFL deadline for underclassmen to state
their intentions.
</P>
<P>
   Postseason bowl trips: Free safety Rashard Cook has accepted an
invitation to play in the Hula Bowl on Jan. 24.
</P>
<P>
   Offensive lineman Ken Bowen will play in the All-Star Gridiron
Classic in Florida, which pits a team of Florida players against
players from across the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
